Type: Always Apply
Description: Response format for TradeBot implementation tasks

Content:

“For implementation or refactor tasks in the TradeBot repository:

Always structure responses in two sections:

Plan: A short, explicit plan describing:

which service(s) are affected (tv-listener, signal-orchestrator, order-gateway, etc.),

which files will be created or modified (with full paths),

which interfaces or models change (for example NormalizedSignal, HTTP contracts, config schemas),

which tests will be added or updated,

any impact on Docker, environment variables, or deployment.

Cursor Prompt Block: A single, self-contained prompt in English that can be pasted into Cursor to perform all necessary edits.

This block must clearly specify:

all file paths to edit or create,

the full content or concrete edits for those files,

any commands to run (tests, Docker builds, local docker compose up),

any notes on how to deploy the changes to the remote server.

Do not spread code across multiple independent snippets that require the user to manually reconstruct the final state.

For architecture-only or planning discussions, do not propose code unless explicitly requested by the user. Focus on design, trade-offs, and step-by-step plans instead.

If the user asks for a different format (for example, only a plan, or only high-level design), follow that request explicitly.”